{
  "texts": [
    "Finally, we use 0-based indexing when referring to blocks, layers, and sequence positions throughout the paper.",
    "For example, \"block 0\" denotes the first block in the Transformer, and \"sequence position 0\" denotes the first token position in a sequence.",
    "In order to avoid ambiguity between \"first\" and index \"1\", we will refer to the \"first\" (0-th) item as the \"initial\" item.",
    "While Transformers are often conceptualized as a sequential operation through each of their components with residual connections between layers, we adopt the mathematically equivalent perspective that these skip connections collectively form the central communication channel through which all components interact.",
    "We refer to this pathway as the residual stream."
  ]
}